				Most recently I led design at [AngelList](http://angel.co "AngelLIst") &mdash; the world’s largest startup community &mdash; where I focused on growing our design team and buildimg our jobs marketplace. Currently, I’m taking some time to travel and reset.  
			
				I’ve been working as a designer for almost 15 years. In that time I’ve designed books, building signage, interfaces, illustrations and more. Like all designers, I dream of one day designing an airplane livery, a chair, and a house. These days, however, I increasingly find myself at the intersection of the digital ‘product’ and ‘design’ disciplines.
				
				I first got into design by making posters and [Bebo ‘themes’](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bebo#Bebo_system) for my friends’ bands and events. Then I took a detour through the somewhat archaic  world of newspaper design. I loved designing newspapers and still think web design can learn a whole lot more from them.

				In my recent career I’ve led a number of deisgn teams. As a design leader, I tend to be more people-focused than pixel-focused — though that dichotomy itself is a huge oversimplification. I truly love working with a team to help them identify, manifest and sustain the ideal conditions for their success. If you work with me, we will have ongoing conversation about ‘how you do your best work’.
		
