				## AngelList
			
				I joined AngelList in 2016 with a mission to make finding a job, or conversely making a new hire, a more human experience. Since then we’ve moved the needle in the right direction, but there’s still a lot to be done. 
				
				Soon after joining the company, I became the fouth person in a ‘skunkworks’ team developing an entirely new product offering — <a href="a-list.co">A&ndash;List</a>. Over the next three years, we grew A&ndash;List into a double-digit-million dollar business. That was a wild ride. 
				
				
				One of my proudest acheivements at AngelList is scaling the design team from two to twelve designers and simulataneusly establishing design as a top-level team in the ogranisation. The deisgn team shipped entirely new products, relaunched existing core products and significantly improved the experience of over 10million job seekers. They also built a new deisgn system, established design principles and were incredibly fun to work with.  
					
				As part of the executive team at AngelList, I contributed to product and business strategy, was integral to delivering key product initiatives, and was part of the deal team on two company acquisitions. 	
				
				### Everything else
					
				Apart from my time at AngelList, I’ve had an intentionally varied career &mdash; from journalist, to designer, to growth-marketer, to design manager. I try to bring what I’ve learnt from each stage with me to the next. 
					
				The two consistent threads have been a focus on narrative and on people. 
	
			
			

