					### Design communities
					Bringing people together to talk about design is something I really enjoy — whether thats a full-scale design event or a dinner or just over a glass of wine. I think every designer should find their own way of contributing back to our field, and giving other designers an opportunity to connect is one way I’ve found to do that.
	
					Between 2013 and 2015 I ran an event called [Design+Banter](http://designandbanter.com/) with my buddy [Sam](https://twitter.com/thesamwillis). We started it to meet other designers and to get to know the design community in London. Its tarted in a bowling alley and ended up as a fully-fledged ‘design event‘. It regularly attracted over 200 attendees a month, sold-out in under a minute and featured world-class design speakers from across the globe. With my move to New York on the horizon, we called it a day in late 2015 after twenty successful events.
	
